HSBC’s Gulliver to Cut Costs at U.K. Retail Arm, Telegraph Says

-- B y   Z i j i n g   W u
-- 
2011-05-01T08:21:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-01/hsbc-s-gulliver-to-cut-costs-at-u-k-retail-arm-telegraph-says.html
HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  Chief Executive
Officer Stuart Gulliver may announce plans to cut costs at the
bank’s U.K. retail unit, the  Sunday Telegraph  reported, without
saying where it got the information.  Gulliver is considering proposals including the sale of
some branches and removing the U.K. retail unit’s head office
staff from HSBC’s global headquarters at  Canary Wharf , the
London-based newspaper said. The plan may be announced on May
11, it said.  An HSBC spokesman declined to comment, according to the
newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zijing Wu in London at   zwu17@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jeff St.Onge at   jstonge@bloomberg.net . 